Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Spread chicken breasts with 2 Tbsp. of the marmalade. Empty coating mix into shallow dish. Add chicken; turn to evenly coat both sides. Place chicken in 13x9-inch baking dish. Bake 25 min. or until chicken is cooked through. Mix dressing with remaining 2 Tbsp. marmalade. Add to spinach; toss to coat. Place 1 chicken breast, sliced on top of each plate and add orange slices, if desired.